      "message": "\u003e Hi Shuhei:\n\u003e \n\u003e I need guidance from you on this change. I want to make report.proto to be available to tools not under tast repo, such as testexecserver, to use. Here are a few questions that I have.\n\u003e \n\u003e 1. Should I make it available in the first place? I don\u0027t see anything wrong with it but I want to check with you first.\n\nYes, it sounds fine.\n\n\n\u003e 2. In my initial patch, I just pick the path \"src/chromiumos/tast/external/protocol. I am not sure if it is the path we want to use. Please let me what is the ideal location for the tast package to expose to non-tast tools.\n\nCan you try putting the package at chromiumos/tast/framework/protocol?\n\nI regret we put both framework codes and user code under the same package prefix, chromiumos/tast. I hope we can clearly split them someday like chromiumos/tast/framework vs. chromiumos/tast/user, though I\u0027m not sure when it will happen.\n\n\n\u003e 3. I think I need to add it to ebuild so it will be emerged, but I don\u0027t know how to do it. Please help.\n\nI think it\u0027s good to introduce a new ebuild that compiles and installs Go bindings of protocol buffers. \n\nThere are a few ebuilds you can take a look at, e.g.\n\nhttps://source.corp.google.com/chromeos_public/src/third_party/chromiumos-overlay/chromeos-base/policy-go-proto/policy-go-proto-9999.ebuild?q\u003dpackage:chromeos%20file:ebuild$%20proto%20file:chromeos-base\nhttps://source.corp.google.com/chromeos_public/src/third_party/chromiumos-overlay/chromeos-base/wilco-dtc-grpc-protos/wilco-dtc-grpc-protos-9999.ebuild?q\u003dpackage:chromeos%20file:ebuild$%20proto%20file:chromeos-base\nhttps://source.corp.google.com/chromeos_public/src/third_party/chromiumos-overlay/chromeos-base/hardware_verifier_proto/hardware_verifier_proto-9999.ebuild?q\u003dpackage:chromeos%20file:ebuild$%20proto%20file:chromeos-base",
